headline: FLY FOR PEANUTS! SOUTHWEST TO SERVE CHARLES M. SCHULZ SONOMA COUNTY AIRPORT IN APRIL 2026
summary: It's a September surprise as Southwest Airlines Co. (NYSE: LUV) is announcing service to Santa Rosa, California's Charles M. Schulz Sonoma County Airport (STS) is set to begin April 7, 2026, with initial flights available for purchase tomorrow morning at Southwest.com®.

headline: T-Mobile US (TMUS) Partners With LA28 As Official Telecom Provider For 2028 Olympics
summary: T-Mobile US (TMUS) recently announced its selection as the Official Telecommunications Services Provider for the Olympic and Paralympic Games in Los Angeles (LA28), a significant event showcasing its advanced 5G solutions. This development, alongside strategic partnerships like its new deal with Southwest Airlines to provide free WiFi, might have bolstered TMUS's 5.1% share price increase over the last quarter. headline: SOUTHWEST AIRLINES TO PRESENT AT THE MORGAN STANLEY LAGUNA CONFERENCE
summary: Southwest Airlines Co. (NYSE: LUV) has been invited to speak at the Morgan Stanley Laguna Conference.
